Auguste and Louis Lumiere are two film makers who created very early films with simple equipment who created films in the late 19th centuary and early 20th centuary. They created actuality films of people going abou their daily lives. The brothers charged patrons to watch 10 short films lasting 50 seconds each with titles such as workers exiting a factory and people bording a train. They also pierneered color photography to add new depth to images.
